{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL pointer dereference in clone_msga_configcommon function\n\n### Summary\nThe `clone_msga_configcommon()` function in `nr_radio_config.c` could crash when trying to encode a NULL `choice.setup` pointer. This issue was caused by missing validation checks before attempting ASN.1 encoding operations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/nr_radio_config.c`: Added NULL pointer checks for `choice.setup` field in all clone functions including `clone_msga_configcommon`, `clone_rach_configcommon`, `clone_pusch_configcommon`, `clone_pucch_configcommon`, `clone_pdcch_configcommon`, and `clone_pdsch_configcommon`.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a gNB with MsgA configuration where `msgA_ConfigCommon_r16->choice.setup` is NULL\n2. Trigger SIB1 generation which calls `clone_msga_configcommon()`\n3. Observe segmentation fault when the function attempts to encode the NULL pointer\n\n### Symptoms\n- Segmentation fault in `clone_msga_configcommon()` when processing NULL `choice.setup` pointers\n- Crash occurs during ASN.1 encoding operations\n- System becomes unresponsive during configuration cloning operations\n\n"
}